<B><a name="loop">Q:</a>  I'm getting this weird loop back to the login screen. Why?  <BR><BR>

A:</B>   If you are using Explorer 5, it is important to have the right time set on your computer's clock - am/pm, date, and time 
zone. If any of these are incorrect, you may not be able to login to the site.  The time is usually located at the bottom right 
of your screen. By simply double-clicking on it you can check the details and change any of the settings. If the clock isn't 
at the bottom right you can get to it by clicking "Start", "Settings", "Control Panel", "Date/Time".

