<B><a name="computer">Q:</a>  Are there any special settings or software that I need for my computer to use this site?<BR><BR>

A:</B>
<ol>
<li>You may not have cookies enabled:  For the staff site, your browser needs to allow cookies. A cookie is a 
temporary Internet file (not made of flour and sugar). Does your computer allow cookies? It is a setting on your 
browser that can be enabled or disabled. In Internet Explorer 5.0, go to the TOOLS menu, then INTERNET 
OPTIONS, then SECURITY tab, then press the CUSTOM LEVEL button, then scroll down to the Cookies section 
and make sure both are ENABLED. <br>
<li>Your web browser may not be compatible:  You may have difficulties if you are not using Internet Explorer version 
5.0 or Netscape Navigator version 4.0 and up on a PC. Check your browser version (i.e. found in HELP, About 
Internet Explorer). You can download free versions of each at their respective websites.  
